sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Ingress as Platform Ingress<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Auth as Auth Proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS<br/>(kube-rbac-proxy / oauth-proxy)
    participant Router as KServe Router
    participant TGIS as vLLM TGIS Adapter<br/>8033/TCP gRPC
    participant HTTP as vLLM HTTP Server<br/>8000/TCP HTTP
    participant Engine as vLLM Engine
    participant GPU as GPU (CUDA)
    participant S3 as Model Storage<br/>(S3 / PVC)

    Note over Engine,S3: Flow 0: Model Loading (Pod Startup)
    Engine->>S3: Load model weights<br/>HTTPS/443 (S3) or volume mount (PVC)<br/>Auth: AWS IAM / HMAC credentials
    S3-->>Engine: Model artifacts / weights
    Engine->>GPU: Load model to GPU memory<br/>CUDA IPC

    Note over Client,GPU: Flow 1: gRPC Inference (TGIS Protocol)
    Client->>Ingress: gRPC request<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+
    Ingress->>Auth: Forward request<br/>HTTPS/8443
    Auth->>Router: Authenticated request
    Router->>TGIS: GenerationService.Generate<br/>gRPC/8033 (pod-internal, no TLS)
    TGIS->>Engine: Python IPC (in-process)
    Engine->>GPU: Tensor operations<br/>CUDA IPC
    GPU-->>Engine: Inference result
    Engine-->>TGIS: Generated tokens
    TGIS-->>Router: gRPC response
    Router-->>Auth: Response
    Auth-->>Ingress: Response
    Ingress-->>Client: gRPC response<br/>TLS 1.2+

    Note over Client,GPU: Flow 2: OpenAI-compatible HTTP Inference
    Client->>Ingress: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+
    Ingress->>Auth: Forward request<br/>HTTPS/8443
    Auth->>Router: Authenticated request
    Router->>HTTP: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>HTTP/8000 (pod-internal, no TLS)
    HTTP->>Engine: Python IPC (in-process)
    Engine->>GPU: Tensor operations<br/>CUDA IPC
    GPU-->>Engine: Inference result
    Engine-->>HTTP: Generated tokens
    HTTP-->>Router: JSON response
    Router-->>Auth: Response
    Auth-->>Ingress: Response
    Ingress-->>Client: JSON response<br/>TLS 1.2+

    Note over Client,HTTP: Flow 3: Health Check
    Client->>HTTP: GET /health<br/>HTTP/8000
    HTTP-->>Client: 200 OK
